  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 88201f4f4f3247558c87e55aa4fb8ac4, type: 3}
  m_Name: GinnyOpening
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: HiddenHarbours.World::HiddenHarbours.World.DialogueDef
  Id: dialogue.ginny_first
  FirstLines:
  - 'Oh, child — you made it out to the island. Your uncle Ned thought the world of
    you, you know.'
  - 'He's gone to the deep now, rest him. He left you his cottage and his memory —
    but the old dory of his is past mending, and there''s no boat handed to you here.'
  - 'No matter. We earn our way on this coast. When the big tide drops, the flats out
    front bare — get the shovel and dig CLAMS where you see the two little squirts.'
  - 'Then the sandbar to Greywick opens up, dry enough to walk. Go before the flood
    seals it, mind — dawdle and you''re stuck till the next low.'
  - 'In Greywick, sell your clams, buy a COD LICENCE and a ROD, and save. There''s a
    damaged dory for sale at the shipwright — buy her, pay to put her right, and she''s
    truly yours.'
  - 'Then sail her home to Coddle Cove. That''s where your harbour starts. Off you go,
    now — the tide won''t wait on us.'
  RepeatLines:
  - 'Back already? Good. Watch the tide — clams on the flats at low water, then the
    bar to Greywick.'
  - 'Sell, licence, rod, then buy and mend that dory. Earn her, and she''ll be yours
    for good.'
